        <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center text-secondary mb-12">Safe Social Media</h2>
          
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-8">
            <!-- Risks & Benefits -->
            <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-lg">
              <div class="card-body">
                <h3 class="card-title text-xl text-secondary mb-4">Risks &amp; Benefits of Social Media</h3>
                
                <!-- Positive aspects -->
                <h4 class="font-semibold mb-3">Positive aspects for tweens &amp; teens</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-4">
                  <li>Connection &amp; belonging – keeps friendships alive after school and lets rural or marginalized youth find supportive communities online<Cite id="surgeon2023" /></li>
                  <li>Creativity &amp; self-expression – platforms allow kids to showcase art, music, coding projects and build digital-portfolio skills valued by colleges and employers<Cite id="surgeon2023" /></li>
                  <li>On-demand learning – short tutorials teach everything from language phrases to CPR, making “just-in-time” learning easy<Cite id="surgeon2023" /></li>
                </ul>
                
                <!-- Key risks -->
                <h4 class="font-semibold mb-3">Key risks to monitor</h4>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-4">
                  <li>Mental-health strain – daily use &gt; 3&nbsp;h is linked to roughly doubled odds of anxiety or depression, and the U.S. Surgeon General warns social media is not yet proven safe for youth<Cite id="surgeon2023" /></li>
                  <li>Cyberbullying &amp; harassment – 46&nbsp;% of U.S. teens report being targeted online, with older teen girls at highest risk<Cite id="vogels2022" /></li>
                  <li>Privacy &amp; data tracking – a 2024 FTC report found major platforms collected and indefinitely stored vast troves of teen data, exposing them to identity-theft, stalking and invasive ads<Cite id="ftcSurveillance2024" /></li>
                  <li>Sleep &amp; attention impacts – late-night scrolling erodes sleep quality; heavy users show shorter sleep duration and next-day focus problems<Cite id="pirdehghan2021" /></li>
                </ul>
                
                <!-- Age-appropriate tips -->
                <h4 class="font-semibold mb-3">Age-appropriate platform tips</h4>
                <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-4">
                  <table class="table table-zebra w-full text-sm">
                    <thead>
                      <tr>
                        <th>Age</th>
                        <th>Recommended approach</th>
                        <th>Why it matters</th>
                      </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                      <tr>
                        <td>Under&nbsp;13</td>
                        <td>Stick to closed ecosystems (family messaging, school apps) &amp; postpone mainstream social apps</td>
                        <td>COPPA and AAP guidance set 13 as the minimum for Instagram, Snapchat, TikTok<Cite id="ftcCoppa" /><Cite id="aapIntroSM2025" /></td>
